    reasoning: '`unattributed` is described as an optional flag. "Not exactly true" presumably means `Some(true)` is the only skip case, with `None` and `Some(false)` both drift-checked. The word "exactly" recurs at line 73 and line 82 (for hashes), suggesting the author is guarding against some looser comparison, but the looser alternative is never named.'
